{
  "text": "\u00ae yarn (polyparaphenylene terephthalamide), 12 \u00b5m filament diameter, 1.44 g/cm [CITATION_1] density was purchased from Goodfellow Cambridge, Huntingdon, England. Acetic acid (BDH, VWR, Dorset, UK) and silane coupling agent A-174 (3-Trimethoxysilyl propylmethacrylate, Merck, Frankfurt, Germany) were used for fiber surface treatment. For the semi-IPN system, Bis-GMA and TEGDMA were purchased from Esschem Europe, PMMA (Mw~350,000 g/mol), TiO 2 (nanopowder, <100 nm particle size) and Benzoyl peroxide (BPO) were supplied by Aldrich, Dorset, UK. everStick \u00ae POST from Stick Tech, Turku, Finland was used as a commercial reference.",
